 Hyderabad Civil Services Rules-Rule 299(1)(b)- Interpretation of Maximum pension payable to a government servant is Rs. 1000 and not Rs. 857.15 per month in Government of India Currency. Government Notification dated February 3,1971 amending cl. (b) of sub-rule (1) of rule 299 not valid.
 States Reorganization Act, 1956-Proviso to sub-s. (7) of s. 115-When applicable Pension is a condition of service and any change made by Government in pension disadvantageous to government servant must comply with requirements of proviso to sub-s. (7) of s. 115.
 Words and Phrases-'Pension'-Pension is a condition of service.
 
